---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ContributionsPage from '../../../components/ContributionsPage';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const imgContributionMatrix = `${base}research-questions/contribution-types-matrix.png`;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Contribution"
  description="Track your research contributions — theory, practice, and methodology"
>
  <p class="back-link"><a href={`${base}research-questions/`}>← Research</a></p>
  <h1>Contribution</h1>
  <p class="page-desc">
    Capture contribution statements as you refine your thesis. Label each as theoretical, methodological, or practical —
    you can change the label when you edit an entry.
    <a href="#types-of-contributions" class="page-desc-link">Types of contributions</a> (reference guide).
  </p>

  <details id="types-of-contributions" class="contribution-types-guide">
    <summary class="contribution-types-guide-summary">Types of contributions</summary>
    <div class="contribution-types-guide-body">
      <p>
        This appendix offers a 4&times;5 matrix showing 20 kinds of research contributions. It is not exhaustive&mdash;it
        merely aims to give you some idea of how easy it is to find a contribution in the research on a real-world
        problem.
      </p>
      <p>To make a contribution, you have to find where previous research is inadequate. In general, we find four kinds of inadequacies:</p>
      <ul class="contribution-types-list">
        <li><strong>New:</strong> something that has never been researched before (theoretically and/or empirically).</li>
        <li><strong>Gap:</strong> something that has been researched before, but there are some areas that have been neglected.</li>
        <li><strong>Conflict:</strong> the research about something has competing explanations or inconsistent findings.</li>
        <li><strong>Wrong:</strong> there are parts of the research (theoretical or empirical) that are incorrect, or making wrong assumptions.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>In any real-world problem we may find five areas where a research contribution is possible:</p>
      <ul class="contribution-types-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Theory</strong> is a generalised explanation of things we can observe in the real world and it is not
          specific to a specific time or place. It could be that there is no theory to explain something or that some
          theory has not been tested before. Often puzzles call for the creation of a new theory&mdash;like germ theory
          explained the puzzle of transmission of disease in the 1800s.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Application</strong> is the use of a theory in practice. It could be that a particular theory has not
          been applied to certain places, not used to explain observations, or that a new application of a theory has not
          been investigated before.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Method</strong> is the technique by which results are generated. One may develop a new method, adapt or
          improve old methods or apply methods to theories or data in ways not done before.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Prediction</strong> is when you make an informed guess based on the theory or data about something that
          is not known. It could be a forecast or positing the existence of unknown phenomena (like Mendeleev who
          predicted the existence of new chemical elements based on his periodic table). It could be that a theory makes
          predictions that nobody thought of before, or can enable the construction of a model that can better anticipate
          future events.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Generalisation</strong> is when you extend a theory or finding to a wider range of groups or phenomena
          than was originally intended. It might happen that findings in one country could be generalised to all South
          American countries but that nobody ever tested this, or that a theory about families can be generalised to the
          whole economy, but that nobody ever considered this.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        When we combine the kinds of inadequacy in the research with the possible areas of contribution, we get the
        4&times;5 matrix of 20 kinds of research contributions, shown in the table below:
      </p>
      <figure class="contribution-types-figure">
        <img
          src={imgContributionMatrix}
          alt="4 by 5 matrix: rows Theory, Application, Method, Prediction, Generalise; columns New, Gap, Conflict, Wrong."
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <figcaption>Twenty kinds of research contribution (inadequacy type &times; contribution area).</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <p>To take some examples:</p>
      <ul class="contribution-types-list">
        <li><strong>Application&ndash;Gap:</strong> applying a theory to a neglected area.</li>
        <li><strong>Method&ndash;Conflict:</strong> using a new or improved method to try to settle a disagreement amongst researchers.</li>
        <li><strong>Theory&ndash;Wrong:</strong> showing that old theories are wrong and where they go wrong.</li>
        <li><strong>Prediction&ndash;New:</strong> using a theory or a model to make predictions that are better or have not been made before.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Some contributions may neatly fit in only one cell, but it is quite common for studies to combine contributions
        from more than one cell.
      </p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <ContributionsPage client:load />

  <script>
    function openContributionTypesGuide() {
      const guide = document.getElementById('types-of-contributions');
      if (guide instanceof HTMLDetailsElement) guide.open = true;
    }
    if (window.location.hash === '#types-of-contributions') openContributionTypesGuide();
    window.addEventListener('hashchange', () => {
      if (window.location.hash === '#types-of-contributions') openContributionTypesGuide();
    });
  </script>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .back-link {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  .back-link a {
    color: var(--color-maroon);
  }
  .page-desc {
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 40rem;
  }

  .page-desc-link {
    color: var(--color-maroon);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .page-desc-link:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .contribution-types-guide {
    margin: 0 0 2rem 0;
    max-width: 42rem;
    padding: 0.65rem 1rem;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-maroon);
  }

  .contribution-types-guide-summary {
    cursor: pointer;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--color-maroon);
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }

  .contribution-types-guide-summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .contribution-types-guide-summary::before {
    content: '▸';
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    transition: transform 0.15s ease;
  }

  .contribution-types-guide[open] .contribution-types-guide-summary::before {
    transform: rotate(90deg);
  }

  .contribution-types-guide-body {
    margin-top: 0.85rem;
    padding-top: 0.85rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }

  .contribution-types-guide-body p {
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem 0;
  }

  .contribution-types-list {
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .contribution-types-list li {
    margin-bottom: 0.55rem;
  }

  .contribution-types-list li:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .contribution-types-figure {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;
  }

  .contribution-types-figure img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 520px;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .contribution-types-figure figcaption {
    margin-top: 0.45rem;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    line-height: 1.45;
  }

  :global(.contributions-page) {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  :global(.contributions-setup),
  :global(.contributions-loading),
  :global(.contributions-empty) {
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
  }

  :global(.contributions-setup) {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-gold);
  }

  :global(.contributions-setup code) {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
    padding: 0.1rem 0.35rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  :global(.contributions-error) {
    color: var(--color-maroon);
    padding: 0.75rem;
    background: rgba(113, 32, 56, 0.08);
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  :global(.contributions-add-section) {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  :global(.contributions-add-toggle) {
    padding: 0.55rem 1.1rem;
    background: var(--color-maroon);
    color: #fff;
    border: 2px solid var(--color-gold);
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  :global(.contributions-add-toggle:hover) {
    background: var(--color-maroon-dark);
  }

  :global(.contributions-add-form) {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-maroon);
  }

  :global(.contributions-add-form label) {
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  :global(.contributions-textarea) {
    width: 100%;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    border: 2px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    line-height: 1.5;
    resize: vertical;
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

  :global(.contributions-textarea:focus) {
    outline: none;
    border-color: var(--color-maroon);
  }

  :global(.contributions-format-hint) {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
  }

  :global(.contributions-format-hint code) {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    padding: 0.1rem 0.35rem;
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  :global(.contributions-submit) {
    padding: 0.55rem 1.1rem;
    background: var(--color-maroon);
    color: #fff;
    border: 2px solid var(--color-gold);
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
  }

  :global(.contributions-submit:hover:not(:disabled)) {
    background: var(--color-maroon-dark);
  }

  :global(.contributions-submit:disabled) {
    opacity: 0.6;
    cursor: not-allowed;
  }

  :global(.contributions-list-title) {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-maroon);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
  }

  :global(.contributions-filter-bar) {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.45rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  :global(.contributions-filter-chip) {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.8rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: #fff;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    cursor: pointer;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    transition: background 0.15s, border-color 0.15s, color 0.15s;
  }

  :global(.contributions-filter-chip:hover) {
    border-color: var(--color-maroon-muted);
    background: rgba(113, 32, 56, 0.04);
  }

  :global(.contributions-filter-chip--active) {
    background: var(--color-maroon);
    border-color: var(--color-gold);
    color: #fff;
  }

  :global(.contributions-filter-count) {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    min-width: 1.25rem;
    padding: 0.05rem 0.35rem;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  }

  :global(.contributions-filter-chip--active .contributions-filter-count) {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
  }

  :global(.contributions-count) {
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
  }

  :global(.contributions-list) {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  :global(.contribution-item) {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  :global(.contribution-type-field) {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    border: none;
  }

  :global(.contribution-type-legend) {
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.45rem;
    padding: 0;
  }

  :global(.contribution-type-toggles) {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.45rem;
  }

  :global(.contribution-type-chip) {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.8rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: #fff;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background 0.15s, border-color 0.15s, color 0.15s;
  }

  :global(.contribution-type-chip:hover) {
    border-color: var(--color-maroon-muted);
    background: rgba(113, 32, 56, 0.04);
  }

  :global(.contribution-type-chip--active) {
    background: var(--color-maroon);
    border-color: var(--color-gold);
    color: #fff;
  }

  :global(.contribution-type-radio) {
    position: absolute;
    opacity: 0;
    width: 0;
    height: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  :global(.contribution-type-badge) {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    border-radius: 999px;
    border: 1px solid transparent;
  }

  :global(.contribution-type-badge--theoretical) {
    color: #4a2860;
    background: #ede4f4;
    border-color: #d4c0e4;
  }

  :global(.contribution-type-badge--methodological) {
    color: #2a4a60;
    background: #e4edf4;
    border-color: #c0d4e4;
  }

  :global(.contribution-type-badge--practical) {
    color: #4a4020;
    background: #f4f0e4;
    border-color: #e4d8c0;
  }

  :global(.contribution-type-badge--unset) {
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
    border-color: var(--color-border);
    text-transform: none;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  :global(.contribution-edit) {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.65rem;
  }

  :global(.contribution-content) {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }

  :global(.contribution-content strong) {
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  :global(.contribution-linked-snippets) {
    margin: 0.75rem 0 0.25rem;
  }

  :global(.contributions-show-snippets-btn) {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
  }

  :global(.contribution-linked-snippets-list) {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0.65rem 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.55rem;
  }

  :global(.contribution-linked-snippet-item) {
    padding: 0.65rem 0.75rem;
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  :global(.contribution-linked-snippet-link) {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  :global(.contribution-linked-snippet-link:hover) {
    color: var(--color-maroon);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  :global(.contribution-linked-snippet-paper) {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
  }

  :global(.contribution-meta) {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
  }

  :global(.contribution-actions) {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  :global(.contributions-btn) {
    padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    border-radius: 6px;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    background: #fff;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }

  :global(.contributions-btn-primary) {
    background: var(--color-maroon);
    color: #fff;
    border-color: var(--color-gold);
  }

  :global(.contributions-btn-secondary:hover) {
    border-color: var(--color-maroon-muted);
    background: rgba(113, 32, 56, 0.06);
  }

  :global(.contributions-btn-delete:hover:not(:disabled)) {
    border-color: var(--color-maroon);
    color: var(--color-maroon);
  }

  :global(.contributions-btn:disabled) {
    opacity: 0.6;
    cursor: not-allowed;
  }
</style>
